OL,3,CFour teens drown over Bank Holiday
OL,4,Cweekend amid record-breaking May heat
OL,6,FThe temperature at Kew Gardens,
OL,7,Fsouthwest London, provisionally
OL,8,Freached 34.8C on Monday, having been
OL,9,F32.3C the day before.
OL,11,FForecasters have warned the record
OL,12,Fcould be broken again on Tuesday, with
OL,13,Fan expected high of 35C across large
OL,14,Fswathes of southern England and Wales,
OL,15,Fwhich could even creep up to 36C.
OL,17,FThunderstorms could be sparked in the
OL,18,Fafternoon, which will affect how hot
OL,19,Fit gets, the Met Office said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
